<aside class="fact">
  <h2>Did you know?</h2>
  <p>A day on Venus is longer than a year on Venus!</p>
  <p>Venus rotates so slowly that a single day on the planet lasts 243 Earth
    days. However, it orbits the Sun faster than Earth, completing a year in
    just 225 Earth days. This means a day on Venus is actually longer than its
    entire year!</p>
